categories.title: ElizaOS Development and Community Updates - December 23, 2025

content.text: ElizaOS has launched Eliza Cloud in beta, with plans to ramp up in January 2026. According to Kenk, they're currently onboarding ecosystem builders for feedback before a wider launch that will include PR events and engagement with coding influencers. The 8004 mainnet is scheduled for mid-January, with a push to onboard agents ahead of EthDenver in mid-February. Their goal is to make Eliza Cloud the standard platform for agent registration.

The core development team is actively working on several projects. Stan reported fixing streaming issues on cloud for build mode, making fixes to the Discord plugin, and reviewing monorepo documentation. Odilitime shared 'plugin-wrapped' analytics and is planning to generate promotional images for social media. The team is also discussing cursor analytics and reviewing external AI frameworks like Mastra.

There are some community concerns about token value, with one user expressing frustration about new tokens potentially devaluing existing ones. Odilitime responded that the recent cloud launch represents their 'first real tokenomics engine.' Meanwhile, in the coders channel, a user reported installation errors with the Eliza CLI and shared a screenshot of the error message.

The development team is also sharing interesting resources, including a GitHub repository for a TypeScript AI agent framework and an article titled 'In A World Without Chatbots' that questions current chatbot interfaces. Additionally, a video about lessons learned from building AI browsers was shared and received positive reactions.

categories.title: Recent GitHub Issues in the elizaOS/eliza Repository

content.text:
Several issues have been opened in the elizaOS/eliza GitHub repository by user borisudovicic and others. These include:

1. Issue #6280: A proposal to add a feedback button to the application.

2. Issue #6278: Implementation of chat renaming functionality.

3. Issue #5930: Addressing streaming and state management in the application.

4. Issue #6091: A request to update the Brandkit on GitHub, opened by user 'linear'.

These issues represent ongoing development efforts to improve user experience and functionality in the Eliza project.

categories.title: Recent Pull Requests in elizaOS/eliza Repository

content.text:
Three recent pull requests have been submitted to the elizaOS/eliza repository:

1. PR #6279 by prajwal-pl introduces a feature that improves message service handlers to perform asynchronous operations and optimizes them for cloud platforms.

2. PR #6276 and PR #6277 (which appear to be duplicates) by standujar fix an issue in the core by adding generic type support for custom event handlers.

Between December 23-24, 2025, the elizaos/eliza repository showed moderate activity with 3 new pull requests (with 1 successfully merged), 2 new issues opened, and contributions from 4 active developers during this period.
